  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Community-Based Sustainable Environmental Advocacy and policies in Haiti/DR - SJM</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Main milestones include: over 100 people trained on environmental conservation practices and policy; environmental protection and climate change adaptation actions taken; community-based organisations supported to implement conservation activities; binational learning exchanges; schools reached with environmental education; people reached with environmental protection messages via media and rallies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The beneficiaries will have an increased awareness of sustainable environmental practices and policies, as well as the skills to promote them and advocate for long-term change, which will result in the protection of the area&apos;s natural resources. In addition, the national and binational platforms, will have the capacity to influence high-level decisions in policy, practice and the law. Also, there will be stronger cross-border collaboration between the rural communities and local authorities.</narrative>
  </description>
